Hence, based on the above narrative the objectives of the Bright Future program are the following: 

1. To inspire, train, coach and facilitate young Afghan urban entrepreneurs to set up a successful business; 
2. To provide young urban Afghans with relevant skills, information and access to relevant networks and peers in order to be more connected and find gainful employment; 
3. To scale up Afghan small and medium enterprises (SMEs) in order to generate jobs, boost productivity and bring innovative products and services to the market; 
4. To strengthen the entrepreneurship ecosystem for setting up or expanding businesses, by improving the physical infrastructure and networks and the promotion of positive perceptions of the Afghan economic perspective; 
5. To improve the ease of doing business by relating policies, laws and regulations to a more conducive labor market .

